# Supabase Setup Walkthrough — GPA-S-LMS

## What Was Done

Applied **3 migrations** to the Supabase project **GPA-S-LMS** (`pistwngkqbfjgjtwmgee`, region: `ap-northeast-2`):

| Migration | Tables Created | Details |
|---|---|---|
| `create_core_library_tables` | 6 | [students](file:///c:/Users/Yash/OneDrive/Desktop/GPA-S-LMS/LibraryApp/database.py#856-871), [books](file:///c:/Users/Yash/OneDrive/Desktop/GPA-S-LMS/LibraryApp/database.py#884-898), `borrow_records`, [transactions](file:///c:/Users/Yash/OneDrive/Desktop/GPA-S-LMS/LibraryApp/main.py#980-987), [promotion_history](file:///c:/Users/Yash/OneDrive/Desktop/GPA-S-LMS/LibraryApp/database.py#1081-1096), [academic_years](file:///c:/Users/Yash/OneDrive/Desktop/GPA-S-LMS/LibraryApp/database.py#1211-1222) + 5 performance indexes |
| `create_portal_tables` | 10 | [requests](file:///c:/Users/Yash/OneDrive/Desktop/GPA-S-LMS/LibraryApp/Web-Extension/student_portal.py#95-119), `student_auth`, [notices](file:///c:/Users/Yash/OneDrive/Desktop/GPA-S-LMS/LibraryApp/main.py#11752-11804), [deletion_requests](file:///c:/Users/Yash/OneDrive/Desktop/GPA-S-LMS/LibraryApp/main.py#14500-14550), `user_settings`, `user_notifications`, `book_waitlist`, `access_logs`, [study_materials](file:///c:/Users/Yash/OneDrive/Desktop/GPA-S-LMS/LibraryApp/Web-Extension/student_portal.py#3287-3314), `book_ratings` |
| `disable_rls_for_direct_psycopg2_access` | — | Disabled RLS on all 16 tables |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> RLS was disabled because the app connects via **direct `psycopg2`** (not the Supabase JS SDK). RLS with no policies would block all queries.

## Verification

- ✅ All **16 tables** confirmed present with correct columns, data types, defaults, primary keys, foreign keys, and unique constraints.
- ✅ All **5 indexes** on `borrow_records` and [books](file:///c:/Users/Yash/OneDrive/Desktop/GPA-S-LMS/LibraryApp/database.py#884-898) created for dashboard query performance.
- ✅ Foreign key relationships verified: `borrow_records` → [students](file:///c:/Users/Yash/OneDrive/Desktop/GPA-S-LMS/LibraryApp/database.py#856-871)/[books](file:///c:/Users/Yash/OneDrive/Desktop/GPA-S-LMS/LibraryApp/database.py#884-898), [transactions](file:///c:/Users/Yash/OneDrive/Desktop/GPA-S-LMS/LibraryApp/main.py#980-987) → [students](file:///c:/Users/Yash/OneDrive/Desktop/GPA-S-LMS/LibraryApp/database.py#856-871)/[books](file:///c:/Users/Yash/OneDrive/Desktop/GPA-S-LMS/LibraryApp/database.py#884-898), [promotion_history](file:///c:/Users/Yash/OneDrive/Desktop/GPA-S-LMS/LibraryApp/database.py#1081-1096) → [students](file:///c:/Users/Yash/OneDrive/Desktop/GPA-S-LMS/LibraryApp/database.py#856-871), [deletion_requests](file:///c:/Users/Yash/OneDrive/Desktop/GPA-S-LMS/LibraryApp/main.py#14500-14550) → [students](file:///c:/Users/Yash/OneDrive/Desktop/GPA-S-LMS/LibraryApp/database.py#856-871).

## Next Steps for Render Deployment

Set these **Environment Variables** in your Render Web Service settings:

| Key | Value |
|---|---|
| `DATABASE_URL` | *(Copy from Supabase → Project Settings → Database → Connection String → URI)* |
| `PORTAL_USE_CLOUD` | `1` |
| `FLASK_SECRET_KEY` | *(Any random long string)* |

Then update the **Start Command** to:
```
cd LibraryApp/Web-Extension && gunicorn student_portal:app
```

Redeploy and the portal will connect to this Supabase database automatically.
